    <item>
      <title>Aili: VLC for body sensing</title>
      <link>http://vlc.lightiot.co/post/aili/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Oct 2017 12:57:59 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://vlc.lightiot.co/post/aili/</guid>
      <description>At Ubicomp&amp;rsquo;17, Tianxing Li form Dartmouth College introduce Aili, a table lamp able to reconstruct a 3D hand skeleton in real time, requiring neither cameras nor on-body sensing devices thanks to visible light.
Aili consists of an LED panel in a lampshade and a few low-cost photodiodes embedded in the lamp base. Aili reconstructs the 3D motion by sensing the panel light-beam obstruction by the hand.
This work shows original application of VLC in the field of sensing.</description>
    </item>
    
